# Autoria Backend (AutoRia clone – API)

Node.js + TypeScript backend for a simplified AutoRia-like platform.

The project exposes a REST API for:

- user registration & login (JWT auth)
- roles & account types (BASIC / PREMIUM)
- creating and managing car advertisements
- profanity checking and review flow
- statistics for PREMIUM sellers
- managing car brands and brand requests

> **Important:** this is an API-only project (no frontend).
> All flows are tested via Postman collection.

---

## Tech stack

- **Node.js** + **TypeScript**
- **Express**
- **MongoDB** (via Mongoose)
- **JWT** for authentication
- **Docker** – used to run MongoDB in a container
- Simple in-memory service for currency rates (mocked)

---

## Project structure (short)

- `src/main.ts` – app entry point
- `src/configs/config.ts` – DB connection
- `src/middlewares/auth.middleware.ts` – JWT auth guard
- `src/auth/*` – auth routes & controllers (`/auth/register`, `/auth/login`)
- `src/modules/users/*` – user model, upgrade to PREMIUM
- `src/modules/ads/*` – ads model, controller and routes
- `src/modules/brands/*` – brand model, brand request model and routes
- `src/services/currency.service.ts` – currency conversion (mocked PrivatBank rates)

---
Test users (mock data for checking flows)

For easier checking, you can create the following users via Postman:

BASIC seller

email: seller1@example.com

password: Password123!

role: SELLER

accountType: BASIC

PREMIUM seller

email: seller@example.com

password: Password123!

role: SELLER

accountType: PREMIUM

---

Running the app (without Docker)
# development
npm run dev

# production build
npm run build
npm run start

---

## Environment variables

Create a `.env` file in the project root (you can use `.env.example` as a template):

```env
PORT=3000
MONGO_URI=mongodb://127.0.0.1:27017/autoria
JWT_SECRET=your-jwt-secret-here
